# Key Observations

- MI-FGSM causes significantly higher degradation compared to FGSM for both models.
- The Original model achieves higher Clean BERTScore but suffers larger BLEU degradation under attacks.
- The LoRA model shows improved robustness in terms of lower BLEU-4 drop percentages.
- LoRA fine-tuning improves METEOR but slightly lowers Clean BERTScore.
- Gradient-based attacks substantially affect n-gram based metrics more than semantic similarity (BERTScore).

---

# Preliminary Conclusion

LoRA fine-tuning improves relative robustness against transfer-based adversarial attacks in terms of BLEU degradation, though semantic similarity (BERTScore) remains relatively stable across both models.

Further large-scale evaluations and additional attack strategies are planned.
